<br>
After this whole thing is dealt with,Gabrielle is going to have to have a good conversation with Yakut about whats been happenin in TRV and such. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uamazondelerium.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Amazon DeLerium</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amazon</span><br>  Posts: 228<br> <font color=#993300>(1/26/02 12:36:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=332.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> As everyone arrives</span><hr size=1> ~ The Princess sat back watching everyone arrive, waiting for the other council members to join them, she looked out the window, it had finaly stopped snowing, it felt like it has been snowing forever. She sat back and sighed, in a way she was glad that Hippolyte and herself could not vote on this trial, it made it alot more easier, on both of them, but she did hope that it was not going to be a biased trial due to friendships...~ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/usheyala.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sheyala</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 355<br> <font color=#993300>(1/26/02 8:26:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=332.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.imaginaire.nu/sailorpluto/images/anime/pluto/72.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: As everyone arrives</span><hr size=1> ~*~ Sheyala also gave a reassuring smile to Zelia.  She didn't personally know this girl..which also meant that she held nothing together.  Shey's vote would be a fair one--and that was why she smiled, so that Zelia would relax..~*~<br>
