<br>
She acknowledges most everyone there with a glance and a slight nod,though not showing much emotion. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ugoddesseris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goddess Eris</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/chaoticdiscordxx/images/eris2.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 68<br> <font color=#993300>(1/30/02 1:02:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=332.topic&index=41>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Oh boy...a trial...</span><hr size=1> ::Eris appeared....quietly cloaked by invisibility to those gathered, except to any Olympian God of Goddess. She walked in with a happy smile and walked over to Zelia, she walked around the girl and giggled, this was going to be fun to watch...Who would of thought, Hera's and Artemis's blessed amazons, in disaray, killing there own kind...how genious. Anyway, she saw the whole thing, even saw what the Princess did. She respected the Princess more after that little war....But she would sit down and watch, quietly, to see what happened.<br>
